 test, but that might not be necessary. I'm focused on preparing the Forge workflow for a library issue, particularly whether it requires setup beyond the usual generated test scaffold. My guidance suggests using action advisory_preparation if there’s non-empty input. However, there's a risk that system property names vary between JVM argument styles. Plus, Java 25 seems to have a different flag format to note.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing native image setup**\\n\\nI'm exploring the usage of `-D` as a system property in native images managed by SubstrateVM, particularly focusing on the native runtime. There's a need for a phrase that clarifies adding runtime arguments for the native test executable. I’m considering when to apply generated tests if `libraryVersion == '5.0.1'`, but I feel we shouldn't apply universally to Netty 4.2.x. Also, my summary will include mentioning the resolved artifact with Vert.x dependencies, but not docker. Should I highlight that local Vert.x HttpServer could be used for test setup instead of an external endpoint?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test setup options**\\n\\nI’m thinking about using a local Vert.x HttpServer on 127.0.0.1 instead of relying on external services, which makes sense for test-code setup. I feel like I should opt for \\\"no_action\\\" unless there’s something concrete to address. Research suggests that for normal usage, a WebClient needs an HTTP server to provide meaningful test coverage, potentially using an in-process local HttpServer. But then, I wonder if that setup goes \\\"beyond normal scaffold\\\"?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing OAuth2 dependency**\\n\\nI’m looking at the library POM, which has an optional vertx-auth-oauth2 that seems necessary for the OAuth2WebClient class. It’s possible that “meaningful coverage” means including a broader API, so an optional dependency might be important, but the existing tests don't seem to have that. I should evaluate whether we need to add a deterministic dependency. The POM notes that this optional dependency isn’t transitively pulled in. I'll check the documentation for more insights on this!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_zoEQPdduXkAWl4PPWAMUcegH|fc_0aee72eb65498026016a41fc32e64c81949bcbba3a4d6a2126", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request, re\nreq=urllib.request.Request('https://vertx.io/docs/vertx-web-client/java/', headers={'User-Agent':'Mozilla/5.0'})\nhtml=urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=20).read().decode('utf-8','replace')\ntext=re.sub('<[^>]+>',' ',html); text=re.sub(r'\\s+',' ',text)\nfor term in ['OAuth2', 'auth', 'Caching', 'session']:\n    inds=[m.start() for m in re.finditer(term, text, flags=re.I)]\n    print(term, inds[:5])\n    for i in inds[:2]: print(text[max(0,i-250):i+450])\nPY", "timeout": 60}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2421, "output": 1316, "cacheRead": 24064, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27801, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782709278200, "responseId": "resp_0aee72eb65498026016a41fc1eaa1c81948b9f980b722aeac8"}}
