[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating library setup**\n\nI'm considering looking at the POM version and whether the netty parent properties use Unsafe. I wonder if I need to run a Java test, but that might not be necessary. I'm focused on preparing the Forge workflow for a library issue, particularly whether it requires setup beyond the usual generated test scaffold. My guidance suggests using action advisory_preparation if there’s non-empty input. However, there's a risk that system property names vary between JVM argument styles. Plus, Java 25 seems to have a different flag format to note.\n\n**Analyzing native image setup**\n\nI'm exploring the usage of `-D` as a system property in native images managed by SubstrateVM, particularly focusing on the native runtime. There's a need for a phrase that clarifies adding runtime arguments for the native test executable. I’m considering when to apply generated tests if `libraryVersion == '5.0.1'`, but I feel we shouldn't apply universally to Netty 4.2.x. Also, my summary will include mentioning the resolved artifact with Vert.x dependencies, but not docker. Should I highlight that local Vert.x HttpServer could be used for test setup instead of an external endpoint?\n\n**Considering test setup options**\n\nI’m thinking about using a local Vert.x HttpServer on 127.0.0.1 instead of relying on external services, which makes sense for test-code setup. I feel like I should opt for \"no_action\" unless there’s something concrete to address. Research suggests that for normal usage, a WebClient needs an HTTP server to provide meaningful test coverage, potentially using an in-process local HttpServer. But then, I wonder if that setup goes \"beyond normal scaffold\"?\n\n**Analyzing OAuth2 dependency**\n\nI’m looking at the library POM, which has an optional vertx-auth-oauth2 that seems necessary for the OAuth2WebClient class. It’s possible that “meaningful coverage” means including a broader API, so an optional dependency might be important, but the existing tests don't seem to have that. I should evaluate whether we need to add a deterministic dependency. The POM notes that this optional dependency isn’t transitively pulled in. I'll check the documentation for more insights on this!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0aee72eb65498026016a41fc1fef1881949763d2d48906e002\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqQfwyTt56qk3Zb1kvs7qWhsFn7M-gja9Jj5KcB_7dgxWBxK6LoQqeH5DeNQqN9a6OW-2A7U9yQ2Il0GT2oKwFC7CvmVvC4O3WRqmODYOh4-LJw_bJeDqZCIQ2iR3uHNMzNU7IxiQiznB3LygwGA_ckQmZuITB2Qp76sL1N0ev4rAFKsCae3q3NA-z5GJauKAohrOpa009F-TgvR__UeaJKUjRb_JBkswCXuftUrZgiCqhqMX54NxSpbghN8qu01S-mj5RYIPxU576WSTHfnY3uSN-limvkABcWsj6ztaa02eblMvfna-iv4T30OxA0909qRiKU5Yo-9eUdVbx2nZ6xYuLfkRq9pjB_4wqQTUfn09ulG3ngoeZ85RpF3GLzseH2DEGj9aV51p-Yg1U5WMs-jeUebNNsR4y2IYHQkdZM2Fh4Ejt2_VwvVtcxRCBGUndnRP1DP-XWGXB9tsA6MRwcx97POQfnk923acUMJvm35IHiECj0akCv4OZVkUgt5QAQmeLaduYd10-ponZcIbRMBmWgKryDj5VF9pJd4vkoSyLjFcTGHY2q1AkwZK0FFCo2tdYAZ6IqL5v8OeJMP5nnhQcKtLZgkeEENtWUj4isWhnw3mz4R1DEY63ASsf6OSROQJAIYjMxV_tjgLm31K4gAs44XVw-t3SxWu1VX5FlLJkc8--9YOK84_-bo2571-ovSyk7920GQlamGHMTiQeau5fK3JpYL0KGg6Xznqq0s9AeeXUbC0q-aWHaTZhYLIPVCm8jWinA5N6NPZblA5_OZjpq2SSfqd-C_SYnPSDtYNw2EKecIbYmbLpZkDUsKvPM0uoc5cuRwYMtF2Qy-iV6yqUPW4VyfivzmQbZUCjx0sJ3i1yD-f95dLeXghXk7JhSHBvpv2FLEDvfAt1JClGhFHuRHLQcnGz_G6L5faWJACkkC5aBo9xVjCGnKmmmXXmx2pyix2SiAn-m5yqSRrsniPPHioc80iDAFrQt3pcLDP1j_TTPhnM3jGtwCIiDc-0bOs53-x-6RW_IjHJJA6hmUlh7K0DxR-b32yseVhJyJwedKHtwYFLDlBcW5blX_xKLU30cASM6v06VUd0LNETW4OwLHhnTWkk4uD3zMjb3wcWYBG8Sw2oq2EkVcsmWAEknAw_xFeCjmYxSOu9cDKbpzDPj4R9TlmAoMkTrr01_sWuQ_O8_lQlz9tfi4awSjXN4KPA8T5TYRKES7TyJBiHjxEndLKFn_DdxMfV79o4u2Z1Mopc8qwS0FHeDlURzNPCSUiHroNnhhjBjX5_fc_B3dvCQmEjEubO2KhAUqbZld3Gj4gcl-Ju-0hVXS1dKkTPkFjB61pxtdcZEj8ELUGBkGVV4-WmTpaXJrCHg38msmQ8sZx_zwisF228FmB4Q8jCGz9yUCEhd82PTn4wpnfjOwUVyOcmvaShCPEPnEZHdE1MUXwyQmyquao8zLfe0z2A1M6QpGFdKO0sSgMYsqa_lZcfwmf0BK